.prettierrc.json file content
{
"trailingComma": "es5",
"tabWidth": 2,
"semi": true,
"singleQuote": true
}

npm install --save-dev prettier
or settings from Format
{
"editor.formatOnSave": true,
"editor.defaultFormatter": "esbenp.prettier-vscode",
"prettier.printWidth": 80,
"prettier.tabWidth": 2,
"prettier.useTabs": false,
"prettier.semi": true,
"prettier.singleQuote": true,
"prettier.trailingComma": "all",
"prettier.arrowParens": "always"
}

Configure Prettier Scripts in package.json
Update your package.json file to include scripts for formatting files using Prettier. Add the following lines to the scripts section:
"scripts": {
"format": "prettier --write \"src/\*_/_.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}\""
}
